"(290 kJ) and 2 g of protein per 100 ml. \n# The use of dried whole milk\nIn order to achieve the same concentration as with the previous recipe using cow's milk, whole dried milk should be reconstituted with one weight unit of milk for 11 weight units of water (or one volume unit of milk for 5 volume units of water). The water should be previously boiled and allowed to cool off completely; sugar should be added. In other words:\n9 15 g of milk powder; 9 170 ml of boiled and cooled water; 9 15 g of sugar."